    <img src="http://www.mediacurrent.com/sites/default/files/imagecache/thumb_blog_spotlight/openshift.png" alt="" title=""  class="imagecache imagecache-thumb_blog_spotlight imagecache-default imagecache-thumb_blog_spotlight_default" width="200" height="152" /> <p>An interesting platform I came across recently for developing and deploying cloud applications is  <a href="https://www.openshift.com/">OpenShift</a> by <a href="http://www.redhat.com">RedHat</a>. OpenShift is a  next generation application hosting platform. The software running this service is open-sourced under the name <a href"http://openshift.github.io/">OpenShift Origin</a>, and is available on <a href="http://www.github.com">GitHub</a>. Developers use <em>Git</em> to deploy web applications in different languages to the platform.</p>
